description:
&lt;p&gt;A vacancy exists for a Full Time AFC Band 4 Payroll Officer with NHS Wales Shared Services Partnership (NWSSP) based in Companies House Cardiff. The successful post holder will work as part of a payroll team providing a payroll service to NHS Wales Organisations. The duties of the successful post holder include, input of permanent entry onto ESR; data verification; sickness absence; occupation and statutory parental schemes; application and management of AEOs; calculation and management of TIA. provide direction and training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful post holder must be experience working in an NHS Payroll Team and must have a working knowledge of the Agenda for Change (AFC) Terms and Conditions of Service; Medical and Dental Terms and Conditions of Service; NHS Wales employment related policies. In addition, the successful post holder must have a working knowledge of ESR; Microsoft Excel; Microsoft Team and NHS Pension.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful post holder will be required to respond to payroll enquiries and have the ability to converse with employees at all levels. Employee will be required to manage employee enquiries in a timely manner via Actionpoint.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful post holder will have the benefit of the opportunity for membership of the NHS Pension Scheme and generous Annual Leave entitlement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held via Microsoft Teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 12/11/2020 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Mrs Susan Hayes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Senior Payroll Supervisor&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Susan.hayes@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 02920 90 3908 &lt;/p&gt;
